Executive Profile
Kristina   Salen  Director, Cornerstone OnDemand, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships46$312,593
Background

		Ms. Kristina Salen serves as a Research Analyst of Fidelity Group Large-Cap Equity Strategies in the media and communications as well as raw materials and utilities sectors. Ms. Salen served as the Chief Financial Officer at Etsy, Inc. since January 2013 until March 31, 2017. Ms. Salen served as Portfolio Manager of Fidelity Investments, Fidelity Charles Street Trust - Fidelity Series Broad Market Opportunities Fund, Variable Insurance Products IV - Telecommunications ... Portfolio, Fidelity Variable Insurance Products-Telecommunications Portfolio, Fidelity Select Portfolios - Multimedia Portfolio, Fidelity Central Investment Portfolios LLC - Fidelity Telecom Services Central Fund, Fidelity Rutland Square Trust II - Fidelity Strategic Advisers Value Fund and Fidelity Commonwealth Trust II - Fidelity Strategic Advisers Value Fund. Ms. Salen served as Portfolio Manager of Fidelity Advisor Series I - Fidelity Advisor Stock Selector All Cap Fund. She served as an Assistant Vice President of Oppenheimer Capital LLC. She joined the Oppenheimer Capital in 2002. Prior to Oppenheimer Capital, Ms. Salen served as an Analyst of Consumer Sector at Merrill Lynch Investment Managers for 4 years and a Retail Analyst of Lazard Freres for 2 years. She served as a Portfolio Manager of Fidelity Capital Trust - Fidelity Stock Selector All Cap Fund. She began her investment career as an Associate at SBC Warburg. She has been a Director of Cornerstone OnDemand, Inc. since July 08, 2014. Ms. Salen holds a BA in Political Science from the Vassar College and holds an MBA in Finance from the Columbia University. She was a Fulbright Scholar.Read Full Background




